did.abstract: This collection consists of approximately 1,300 CDs representing the work of musicians local to the Washington Area, including Maryland and Northern Virginia. Additionally, the collection holds financial records, marketing material, recordings, photographs, meeting minutes, fundraising records, production records, correspondence, articles, memos, meeting minutes, press releases, early organizational records, and other official papers that document the work of the Washington Area Music Association from 1984 to 2016. The collection was compiled by the non-profit Washington Area Music Association (WAMA) as part of their mission to promote the work of local artists.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of approximately 1,300 compact discs (CDs) and other audio recording formats such as DVDs, pocket CD-Rs, VHS tapes and casette tapes, featuring the music of a wide variety of artists local to the Washington D.C. and Northern Virginia/Maryland area. Additionally, the collection features the files, information, and other records of WAMA while the organization was functional. The materials range in date from 1984 to 2016; the bulk of the material dates to between 1994 and 2001. This collection of recordings and paper records were originally compiled by the Washington Area Music Association (WAMA), a non-profit organization of music industry professionals dedicated to promoting and celebrating the work of Washington Area Musicians.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Washingon Area Music Association (WAMA) is a non-profit organization of music industry professionals dedicated to promoting and celebrating the work of musicians from the Washington and Northern Virginia/Maryland area. Founded in 1985, the organization consists of a board of directors and an advisory board composed of musicians, managers, recording engineers, record industry professionals, lawyers, and others with an active role in the Washington area music community. The organization is run entirely through the effort of volunteers. WAMA sponsors the annual "Wammies" award show, which honors local musicians for achievement in a wide variety of music genre, reflecting the diversity of the DC music scene. WAMA also hosts charitable events and provides services to DC musicians, such as a music calendar, musician directory, and seminars on topics relating to the music business.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Arranged into 8 series: Recordings of Washington area musicians on CD format, Recordings of Washington area musicians on non-CD formats, Governance, Productions, Audio/Visual materials, Artist/Band Promotional materials, Published materials and Photographs and posters.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Gift of Washington Area Music Association, 2014 August 27, (2014.029) and 2018 May 17, (2018.020).

did.unittitle: Recordings of Washington area musicians on non-CD formats

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of a small number of recordings of musicians local to the Washington Area, including Maryland and Northern Virginia, in alternative formats (one pocket CD-R, two cassette tapes, two DVDS and one VHS tape).

did.unittitle: Recordings of Washington area musicians on CD format

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of approximately 1,190 CDs representing the work of musicians local to the Washington Area, including Maryland and Northern Virginia. Many of the artists and specific albums represented here have been recognized by the Washington Area Music Association at their annual "Wammies" award ceremony. Among the diverse genres represented are Bluegrass, Blues, Country, Electronic, Jazz, Latin, Punk Rock, Reggae, Rock, World, and more.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is subdivided into 29 subseries, arranged alphabetically by genre and ending with Undetermined Genre: Bluegrass; Blues; Celtic; Children's; Classical; Country; Easying Listening; Electronic; Folk; Folk Rock; Funk/Funk Rock; Gospel/Religious; Hip Hop; Holiday; Jazz; Latin; Metal; Musical Soundtrack; New Age; Pop; Punk/Post-Punk; Rap; Reggae; Rhythm & Blues/Soul; Rock; Spoken Word; Swing/Big Band; World; Subseries 29: Undetermined Genre

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of the papers and processes from when the WAMA foundation was a working organization, documenting the bodies and tools of governance.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains the administrative records of WAMA from its inception in 1984 to 2004. The materials include office records, correspondence, marketing material, production records, publications, and other early organizational records.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries documents records relating to the Board of Directors, include annual reports, meeting agendas and papers, meeting transcripts, and meeting minutes, Word-for-word transcription of many of the Board of Director's meetings, as well as collections of Board materials and meeting agendas reflect broadly the priorities of the WAMA foundation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Finance Records document well the financial activities and concerns of the WAMA foundation, the condition of the program's finances throughout part its history, and the various changes in procedures and policies concerning financial matters.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is arranged in to two subseries: Wammies and Crosstown Jam.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: It docments the records for WAMA's annual Crosstown Jam, a citywide music festival, and fundraising event, and the Wammies, a local music awards program.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The subseries includes flyers, posters, postcards, press releases, programs, and correspondence. The material relates to the productions undertaken by WAMA to produce its annual Wammies music awards.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The subseries includes flyers, posters, postcards, press releases, programs, and correspondence. The material relates to the productions undertaken by WAMA to produce its annual Crosstown Jams music festival.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series is comprised of VHS cassettes, CDs, and two vinyl records.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The series is grouped by audio/visual type. The VHS cassettes are organized first in chronological order, then the CDs are arranged next alphabetically, and lastly the two vinyl records.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series is comprised of folders, pampletes, business cards, photographs, and other content sent to WAMA from rising artists and bands in the surrounding DC metropolitan area.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
